Yes — this is the right refactor.

In the YAML you shared, `SIT` is hardcoded in the pipeline name, variable group, build-pipeline names, branch validation, stage names, deploy template inputs, backup paths, and build tags. So the clean fix is not just “add one parameter”, but “centralize all environment-specific values and read them from one environment parameter.” 

Also, for this kind of selection, use a **parameter**, not a normal variable. Azure Pipelines parameters are expanded during template parsing, which is exactly what you need for choosing environment-specific structure and template inputs. Normal variables render later and are just strings. ([Microsoft Learn][1])

